column5: I am. I am very familiar with how my body reacts, and I never try and push it to the limit. I always stay very safe with my substance use. I don't wanna die yet. If I was gonna kill myself it would definitely be that way though. Just fall asleep and stop breathing. Easy peasy.
Thanks man. My 21st bday is I'm a few day so I will make a resolution to get fit over the next year.

I do love hiking but I live in fucking Texas in the middle of the plains. No where to hike that ain't like 3 hours away. I do enjoy walks but my city is so bland and ugly. Ain't shit to look at beside the freeway. I do need to start exercising though. Don't do that barely at all. How does it help you?

Thank you man. I have been trying to slow down over the past year and I've done a good job. It's not nearly as bad as it used to be. I'm trying to find something to replace it but it's been rough. I have so little motivation to do anything. Will keep at it though.
Paragraphs man. I like reading people's stories but I can't do a huge block of text. But everything you said rings true for me. Fuck all of it.
I do. I have panic attacks and just curl up and cry. So much pain.

I'm sorry man. People are so quick to try and discredit or sweep depression under the rug. I have people who I know live me and are there for me and I'm still fucked up. I can't imagine having someone telling you your feelings are false or you are wrong about how you feel.
God damn man. And my as want to go on a road trip in Mexico... How safe is it for a tourist driving around Mexico?
